Text.Value: I'll do my very best to fight off my hunger.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Avatar Astarion has the option to tell his companion that he's a vampire spawn.

Text.Value: A vamp, huh? Interesting. Keep your teeth to yourself, Astarion, and we won't have any issues.
So be it. At least this time, you are truthful.
So much as smack your lips when I'm near, and I will sever you piece by piece.
Which means, technically, you're far more easier to kill than a full-fledged vampire. How very fortunate for me.
Hells. What gave me away?
Anyway, you'd burn your tongue off if you went for this neck.
Tsk'va - what is this?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character saw Astarion use his 'bite' ability on someone else (probably in combat, but not necessarily) and confronts him about being a vampire.

Text.Value: *Lae'zel is not exactly the forgiving type. It might be best to keep your bloody secret to yourself.*
Say nothing about your vampirism.
I'll leave you to guess which piece I plan to start with. Now -
Since you'd deny me the entertainment, you'll make me a promise instead.
But let me be clear: so much as smack your lips when I'm near, and I will sever you piece by piece.
Your breath reeks of blood-iron. You slink like a darkling and preen like a parrot.
Which means you are either a halfwit, or you think I am.
So be it. At least this time, you are truthful.
You bit me.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Character was bitten by Astarion in gameplay.
EditorData.logicalname: WAS BITTEN BY AST IN GAMEPLAY

Text.Value: Two punctures deeper than the others; minimal seepage. Shka'keth - a vampire. An undead slinks among us.
No githyanki meals, I promise.
No more lies, Astarion. These wounds you've branded me with tell your bloodthirsty tale.
It's time you know the truth: I'm a vampire. A vampire spawn, technically.
*Lae'zel seems to have a touch of respect for you. Perhaps she'll take the news with grace - or whatever passes for grace for a githyanki.*
I'd just better not wake in the night to find fangs at my throat.
Quite right. We all have our hungers to sate. Some just happen to hunger for blood.
I'll leave you to guess which piece I plan to start with. Am I understood?
Your lie is plain as fangs in your mouth, and still you stand by it.
Yes, loud and clear.
Very well - but I'm keeping an eye on you. And no wisecracks about having us for supper.
Pardon? You think I'm a vampire?
Oh, good. I'd hate to see you subject yourself to my further mockery.
So we're travelling with a vampire, are we?
For now, I'll let you live. I'll even let you keep the privilege of my alliance.
So an undead slinks among us.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Avatar Astarion tried to bite this companion during the night, but you woke up and discovered he was a vampire. You talked it through and resolved things peacefully in CAMP_AstarionHunger_IVB_SCO_Avatar_Choice.lsj

Text.Value: I should have told you earlier. No excuses.
It's time you know the truth: I'm a vampire. A vampire spawn, technically.
Oh, and a quick word of warning, Astarion: I taste absolutely awful. Keep your distance.
We all have our hungers to sate. Some just happen to hunger for blood.
But sweet as my blood is, it is not for the quaffing; luscious as my meat is, it is not to be dined on.
Don't be ridiculous. I'm just a normal elf, an innocent elf.
Chk. Anything less than a full promise is hardly your 'very best'.
But so much as smack your lips when I'm near, and I will sever you piece by piece.
Yeah. And I'm way too hot to touch.
It is to your benefit that you've proven yourself so useful in spite of your - condition.
Given our group's nature, I don't see much harm. We're each monsters in the making, after all.
*Brutal as she is, Lae'zel values honesty. She'll respond fairly and rationally. Maybe.*
You know where I stand. And if you so much as smack your lips when I'm near, I will sever you piece by piece.

EditorData.logicalname: Check more than one party member

Text.Value: I'll let you live. I'll even let you keep the privilege of my alliance. In exchange, you'll keep your fangs away from me and anyone in our group.
Let's consider the subject closed, shall we? Now - is there anything more to discuss?
Don't tell me you intend to cling to this ridiculous deceit.
Well - I'm waiting.
I'm not making you a promise I can't keep.
Of course you are. I may be an outsider to these lands - but I am hardly ignorant of your kind.
Fine - as long as he keeps his fangs off our necks.
What do you have to say for yourself, vampire?
I'm not making you a promise I can't keep.
Fine, I'm a vampire. How did you figure it out?
So we're travelling with a vampire, are we? Of course we are.
A vampire? Well that explains the pallor.
And here I was hoping you'd embarrass yourself with some pathetic justification.
So an undead slinks among us.

Text.Value: I'm not a vampire, Lae'zel. Now drop it.
Your breath reeks of blood-iron. You slink like a darkling and preen like a parrot. You wear your identity like a second skin.
A word of warning, Astarion: I taste absolutely awful.
Chk - a vampire spawn? An undead slinks among us.
It's time you know the truth: I'm a vampire. A vampire spawn, technically.
Is there anything more we should discuss?
Vamps don't scare me. As long as they keep their teeth to themselves.
Am I understood?
I suppose you can't be blamed. Sinewed muscles, sanguine flesh - I must be quite the temptation.
But if you so much as smack your lips when I'm near, I will sever you piece by piece.
Hunting with vampires? Never thought I'd see the day.
It's true - there's no use denying it.
A word of warning, Astarion: I taste absolutely awful. Keep your distance.
You've caught me. Sorry about the bite.
No more lies, Astarion. The wounds you inflicted tell your bloodthirsty tale.
Oh, good. I'd hate to see you subject yourself to my further mockery.
No sense judging someone for who they are. Except devils, obviously.
I am not averse to your kind, Astarion. Queen Vlaakith herself dwells in undeath, and she is no less revered for it - and no less alluring.
Do you think because I'm an outsider that that makes me ignorant?
I'm a vampire spawn, if you want to be technical.
How fortunate for you that I am a reasonable woman.
I've drawn my limits. It would be a great pity for you should you cross them.
You had a choice, Astarion, and you failed me. But I'm not an unreasonable woman.
I've half a mind to slit your neck for the secrecy. It is to your benefit that you've proven yourself so useful in spite of your - condition.
Chk. Anything less than a full promise is hardly your 'very best'.
I'll do my very best to fight off my hunger.
We all have our hungers to sate. Some just happen to hunger for blood.
You've been keeping a secret, Astarion. And I don't like secrets.
